The paper deals with wireless communication and information theory, which suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses network topology and interference, which are relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of coded caching and optimization techniques may also place the paper in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
